dataIdInfo.idAbs:
These boundaries are simplified from the U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service Real Estate Interest data layer containing polygons representing tracts of land (parcels) in which the Service has a real estate interest. Interior boundaries between parcels were dissolved to produce a single set of simplified external boundaries for each feature. These are resource grade mapping representations of the U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service boundaries. For legal descriptions of the land represented here, contact the USFWS Realty Office. This map layer was compiled by the U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service. Although these boundaries represent lands administered by the U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service, not all areas are open to the public. Some fragile habitats need to be protected from human traffic and some management areas are closed. The public is urged to contact specific Refuges or other conservation areas before visiting.

Data can be downloaded here: https://gis-fws.opendata.arcgis.com/datasets/fws::fws-national-realty-tracts-simplified/explore
dataIdInfo.idPurp: This data set depicts simplified boundaries of lands administered by the U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service including National Wildlife Refuges, National Fish Hatcheries, FWS administrative sites, and other conservation areas.

dataIdInfo.suppInfo: The FWS Interest feature class is an aggregated data layer derived by appending separate regional feature data sets into a single national data set that represents land and waters that USFWS has acquired a real estate interest in. (FWS Interest is available at: <https://fws.maps.arcgis.com/home/item.html?id=0a30eaf43328427db8750282d67f0005> ) This data set is a simplified version of the FWS Interest feature class. The spatial and positional accuracy of this information will vary depending on the original source data and methods utilized. All data sources are not listed in this document but are maintained regionally and are available upon request. We strive to improve the accuracy of this data and incorporate more reliable information when available. This dataset does not distinguish Refuges or other areas that are open to the public from those that are closed to the public for any reason. The public is urged to contact specific Refuges for information about public access.

prcStep.stepDesc: Queried parcels are dissolved on CMPXNAME, ORGNAME, DIVNAME, ORGCODE, MGMTCODE, IFWS, LIT, STATUS, INTTYPE1, INTTYPE2, RSL_TYPE, FWSREGION. Summarized on GISACRES

Real estate interest parcels from the U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service Cadastral Data Geodatabase FWSInterest Feature Class are filtered: "INTTYPE1" <> 'E' AND "RSL_TYPE <> 'WPA' AND "RSL_TYPE"<>'FSA' OR ("RSL_TYPE" IS NULL)
The two queried and dissolved sets are merged

Real estate interest parcels from the U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service Cadastral Data Geodatabase FWSInterest Feature Class are filtered: "INTTYPE1" = 'E' OR "RSL_TYPE"='WPA' OR "RSL_TYPE"='FSA' AND ("RSL_TYPE" IS NOT NULL)
Second query is dissolved on CMPXNAME, ORGNAME, DIVNAME, ORGCODE, MGMTCODE, IFWS, LIT, STATUS, INTTYPE1, INTTYPE2, RSL_TYPE, FWSREGION. Summarized on GISACRES

attr.attrdef: Organization Name - Official name given to a Service organization that has been assigned an official five-digit numeric organization code by the Washington Office, Division of Financial Management

attr.attrdef: The current status of USFWS management pertaining to a parcel of a land or water, and whether the parcel is owned and/or managed by the USFWS (Acquired) or is owned and/or managed by another party (Inholding).

edom.edomvd: Inholding - Lands within the approved acquisition boundary for which the FWS has yet to acquire an interest.
Acquired - Parcel for which FWS has fee or less than fee interest.

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: Interest Type 1 - the primary real property interest (land or water) held by the USFWS.

edom.edomvd: Agreement - Lands and waters owned by the United States, States, or others for which the Service has entered into a memorandum of agreement (MOA), memorandum of understanding (MOU), and/or administrative authority to manage the subject lands.

Secondary - Lands and waters owned by the United States, States, or others that are made available to the USFWS for management through permit, cooperative agreement, and overlay or secondary withdrawal.
Partial Interest - Lands and waters where the United States owns a specific interest on or over part of a geographic area, but for which the fee title remains with the landowner.
Fee - Lands owned in Fee title (full rights) by the United States where the Service is the primary administering agency.
Unknown - Lands and waters where the United States is unsure of the legal interest owned and requires further research or supporting documentation of ownership of rights.
None - No legal FWS interest exists (value typically reserved for "Inholding" tracts).
Memorandum - Lands and waters owned by the United States, States, or others that are made available to the USFWS for management through a memorandum of agreement or memorandum of understanding
Easement - Lands and waters where the United States owns an interest in, but for which the fee title remains with the landowner.
Lease - Lands and waters where the United States enters into a lease, typically for a specified term, with a landowner, but for which fee title remains with the landowner.

attr.attrdef: Literals - Unique alpha codes assigned by the Washington Office, Division of Realty, that identify the organizational units, areas, and project sites on Service-owned lands.
attr.attrdefs: USFWS Data Element Standard for Literals

attr.attrdef: Organization Code - Unique five-digit numeric codes assigned by the Washington Office, Division of Financial Management, to Service organizations where personnel are assigned and all unstaffed land management units. Organization codes may also be assigned to meet an administrative requirement. "-9999" is the null value assigned to entities that do not have an Organization Code
Unit Name - Name given to a Service unit of a specific National Wildlife Refuge

attrdomv.udom: Regional National Wildlife Refuge unit list

attr.attrdef: Complex Name - Name of a number of stations combined under one management structure

attrdomv.udom: Regional National Wildlife Refuge Complex list

attr.attrdef: Division Name - Name given to a Service organization division

attrdomv.udom: Regional National Wildlife Refuge division list

attr.attrdef: Organization Type - Administrative categories that identify Service organizations by their primary facility function, program activities, specialized duties and responsibilities, and/or operational status.
attr.attrdefs: USFWS Data Element Standard for Organization Type

edom.edomvd: Farm Service Administration. Lands or interests in lands acquired from the Farm Service Agency, Department of Agriculture, that are not located within existing project boundaries.

National Fish Hatchery. Facility where fish are raised. Hatchery objectives are to replenish depleted stocks, to mitigate federal water projects, to assist with the management of fishery resources on federal lands, and to enhance recreational fisheries.
Coordination Area. Any area administered as part of the National Wildlife Refuge System and managed by the state under cooperative agreements between the Service and a state fish and wildlife agency.
Administrative Site. Land used to support administrative programs, such as maintenance facilities or offices, and offsite visitor centers.

Fish Technology Center. Fish Technology Centers work collaboratively with government, state, university, and private partners to develop new concepts, strategies, and technologies for science-based conservation and management of aquatic resources, focusing on the fields of Conservation Physiology and Ecology, Fish Nutrition and Diet Development, Aquaculture, Fish Passage and Screening, and Sensitive Aquatic Species Conservation.
National Wildlife Refuge. Any area of the National Wildlife Refuge System, except Coordination Areas and Waterfowl Production Areas.

Waterfowl Production Area. Any wetland or pothole acquired pursuant to the Migratory Bird Conservation Act or other statutory authority and administered as part of the National Wildlife Refuge System and identified by county designation
